  "method": [
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Place a non-stick frying pan over a medium-low heat and add the\nbutter. Thinly slice the garlic, add to the pan and cook gently for\nabout 2 minutes until softened but not browned."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Meanwhile, finely chop all of the herbs and set aside."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Lightly beat the eggs in a bowl and stir in three-quarters of the\nherbs. Pour into the pan and crumble in three-quarters of the feta.\nCook gently while stirring all the time until the mixture is just set –\nyou want soft, silky curds."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Plate up, or pop straight on top of some toast. Finish with the\nremaining herbs and feta, the smoked paprika and a good drizzle of\nolive oil."
    }
